      <hedline>
        <hl1>World Briefing | Americas: Colombia: Irishmen Freed From Prison</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Juan Forero (NYT)</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Forero, Juan</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Niall Connolly, James Monaghan and Martin McCauley, who are from Northern Ireland, are freed from Bogota prison two months are being acquitted on charges of teaching bomb-making to rebels (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Three Irishmen linked to the Irish Republican Army were freed from a Bogotá prison, two months after a judge found them innocent of teaching bomb-making to Marxist rebels but convicted them of traveling on false passports. The men, Niall Connolly, James Monaghan and Martin McCauley, were arrested in 2001 after leaving a rebel camp in the south.</p>
        <p>Juan Forero (NYT)</p>
      </block>
